Employee: You are entitled to benefits that are normally only offered to employees. Example:Employer's contribution to CPF;Medical and vacation leave;Medical reimbursement; andGroup accident and health insurance, etc.
Self-employed: You do not receive any protection or benefits from the payer.You provide your own medical and insurance coverage. You are required to contribute to your own CPF Medisave account.You are required to pay employer's CPF contribution to your workers.
